  "answer": "I've completed the research on Fiji visitor arrivals. Here's a summary of the key findings:\n\n## Fiji Visitor Arrivals — Key Findings\n\n### July Peak Season History\n- **July 2025: 99,311** (+1.0% YoY) — new all-time July record\n- **July 2024: 98,332** (+5.2% YoY)\n- **July 2023: 93,483** (+19.3% YoY)\n- **July 2022: 78,368**\n\n**Notable trend for forecasting:** July YoY growth has decelerated sharply each year (+19.3% → +5.2% → +1.0%), suggesting peak-month arrivals are approaching a capacity ceiling around ~99–100k.\n\n### Most Recent Monthly Data\n- **May 2026 = 85,405 (−1.4% YoY)** — the latest published month; July 2026 figures aren't out yet (typically released in August 2026)\n- **2026 YTD:** Jan 70,993 (+0.3%), Feb 54,219 (+9.6%), Mar 71,765 (+12.4%, record), Apr 79,724 (−0.8%), May 85,405 (−1.4%)\n- 2026 momentum is **mixed** — strong Q1 but April/May turned slightly negative YoY\n\n### Context\n- 2025 annual total: **986,367** (record, +0.3% vs 2024)\n- 12-month rolling total hit 999,225 in March 2026 (near 1M mark)\n- Ministry of Finance forecasts 1,003,283 for full-year 2026\n- The June→July month-over-month lift was **+7.1% in both 2024 and 2025** — a consistent seasonal pattern useful for the July 2026 forecast\n\nAll figures are provisional (subject to revision) and sourced primarily from the Fiji Bureau of Statistics, cross-validated with Fiji Times and Mai TV reporting.",
